com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message

Class IndexedArrayOfFields

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.message.IndexedArrayOfFields
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IndexedBytesFieldImporter, Recyclable

    public class IndexedArrayOfFields
extends Object
implements IndexedBytesFieldImporter, Recyclable
    Interface representing an indexed collection of fields and implied field groups.

    Concrete implementations are designed to be used as backing stores for messages and methods are provided to support all operations generally available to message clients via field and field group handles respectively.

    However clients must not make assumptions about how the field and field group return to them are implemented or managed. It is generally recommended that such handles are not cached by clients for any longer than absolutely necessary. They are likely to go out of scope or at least be invalidated when the collection is recycled.

    In terms of how fields and field groups are addressed via this interface:

    • A field group is uniquely identified by (i.e. its coordinates are):
      • The index of its parent field
      • Its ordinality
    • A field is uniquely identified by (i.e. its coordinates are):
      • The coordinates of its field group (see above)
      • Either a key (see IntKeyed), OR an index (i.e. position within the group)

    Each collection has a distinguished group, the root group, to which all root fields belong. This coordinates of this group are (-1, -1) (or, in fact, any combination where both coordinate values are negative).

    See Also:
    FieldProxy, FieldGroupProxy, IndexedArrayOfFieldsElement, IndexedArrayOfFieldAlgorithms
